                \n {"practice":"8","code":"SG-1","subCode":"b) threats addressed by the defense in depth strategy; and","explanation":"The requirement mandates documenting how the product's defense-in-depth strategy mitigates specific threats, ensuring robust security during installation, operation, and maintenance.","context":"Industrial Control Systems (ICS) face diverse threats; documenting threat mitigation strategies aids stakeholders in understanding and implementing security measures effectively.","challenges":["Identifying all relevant threats: Comprehensive threat modeling is complex due to evolving attack vectors. Example: A legacy ICS may lack documentation for modern cyber threats like ransomware.","Aligning threats with mitigation layers: Ensuring each threat is addressed by appropriate security controls. Example: Network segmentation may not mitigate insider threats effectively.","Maintaining updated documentation: Threat landscapes change rapidly. Example: A new zero-day vulnerability may require immediate updates to defense strategies.","Ensuring stakeholder understanding: Technical documentation must be accessible to diverse roles. Example: Operators may misinterpret security controls without clear guidance.","Validating threat coverage: Proof of mitigation effectiveness is often lacking. Example: A vendor claims defense-in-depth but fails to test against advanced persistent threats (APTs)."],"best_practices":[{"description":"Conduct regular threat modeling workshops with cross-functional teams to identify and document threats. Example: A vendor collaborates with OT security experts to model threats for a new PLC.","url":" https://www.siemens.com/global/en/products/automation/industry-software/automation-software/tia-portal.html","url_description":"Siemens TIA Portal documentation includes threat modeling templates for ICS components."},{"description":"Map threats to specific defense layers (e.g., network, host, application). Example: A DCS vendor documents how firewall rules mitigate unauthorized access threats.","url":" https://www.honeywellprocess.com/library/support/technical-notes/Documents/TN-230-EN-ICS-Security-Recommendations.pdf","url_description":"Honeywell's ICS security guide provides threat-to-control mappings for process systems."},{"description":"Use standardized threat taxonomies (e.g., MITRE ATT&CK for ICS) for consistency. Example: A SCADA system's documentation references ATT&CK Tactic TA0043 for threat categorization.","url":" https://www.mitre.org/sites/default/files/2021-10/ATT%26CK-for-ICS-Matrix-1.0.xlsx","url_description":"MITRE's ATT&CK for ICS matrix aids in structured threat documentation."},{"description":"Include real-world attack scenarios in documentation. Example: A vendor documents how Stuxnet-style threats are mitigated via code signing and whitelisting.","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/recommended_practices508.pdf","url_description":"CISA's ICS defense-in-depth guide includes case studies of mitigated attacks."}],"key_aspects":[{"id":"KA1","title":"Threat Identification Methodology","description":"Document the process for identifying threats (e.g., STRIDE, PASTA) to ensure repeatability and coverage. Aligns with SG-1(b) by providing traceability for threat inclusion.","related_links":[{"title":"Rockwell Automation Threat Modeling Guide","url":" https://literature.rockwellautomation.com/idc/groups/literature/documents/wp/enet-wp010_-en-p.pdf","description":"Rockwell's guide for ICS threat modeling methodologies."},{"title":"ISA/IEC 62443-3-2 Threat Identification","url":" https://www.isa.org/standards-and-publications/isa-standards/isa-iec-62443-series-of-standards","description":"ISA standard for systematic threat identification in ICS."}]},{"id":"KA2","title":"Control-to-Threat Mapping","description":"Explicitly link each documented threat to corresponding defense mechanisms (e.g., DMZ for network attacks). Critical for SG-1(b) compliance to demonstrate mitigation coverage.","related_links":[{"title":"Schneider Electric Defense-in-Depth Whitepaper","url":"https://www.se.com/ww/en/work/support/cybersecurity/white-papers/","description":"Schneider's whitepaper on mapping controls to ICS threats."},{"title":"NIST SP 800-82 Rev.3 ICS Controls","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-82r3.pdf","description":"NIST guidelines for ICS security control implementations."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Threat Documentation Templates","description":"Standardized templates ensure consistent threat documentation across product lines. Supports SG-1(b) by enabling clear communication of defense strategies.","related_links":[{"title":"Siemens ICS Security Documentation Toolkit","url":" https://new.siemens.com/global/en/products/automation/industry-software/automation-software/tia-portal.html","description":"Siemens' template library for ICS security documentation."},{"title":"ISA Security Compliance Institute Templates","url":"https://www.isasecure.org/en-US/","description":"ISCI's standardized templates for ICS threat documentation."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Maintenance Procedures for Threat Updates","description":"Define processes for updating threat documentation when new vulnerabilities emerge. Essential for SG-1(b) to maintain current defense-in-depth validity.","related_links":[{"title":"Yokogawa Security Patch Management Guide","url":" https://www.yokogawa.com/solutions/products-platforms/control-system/centum-vp/security/","description":"Yokogawa's approach to updating ICS threat responses."},{"title":"ICS-CERT Advisories Database","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/uscert/ics/advisories","description":"Source for emerging ICS threats requiring documentation updates."}]}],"name":"Product defense in depth","description":"A process shall exist to create product user documentation that describes the security defense in depth strategy for the product to support installation, operation and maintenance that includes